For this task, allocate an Elastic IP address named datacenter-eip using Terraform.
EIP is for: Hosting a public-facing web server.
Ensuring consistent IP for DNS records.
Associating with a NAT gateway for outbound internet access from private subnets.

resource "aws_eip" "datacenter-eip" {
    domain = "vpc"
    tags = {
        Name = "datacenter-eip"
    }
}

and the provider.tf file 
terraform {
required_provider{
aws = {
source = ""
version = ""
}}}
provider "aws" {
region = "us-east-1"}
